DATE: 7 FEB 2026

ASG & SNS 


SNS:
    WHAT IS SNS IN AWS?

    --------------------------------------------------
    SIMPLE DEFINITION
    --------------------------------------------------

        Amazon SNS (Simple Notification Service) is a
        message delivery and notification service in


        It sends messages to people or systems instantly.

    --------------------------------------------------
    WHAT CAN SNS DO?
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Send alerts or notifications  
        • Send messages to email or SMS  
        • Trigger Lambda functions  
        • Notify other AWS services  
        • Push messages to mobile apps  

   
        It is something like  A broadcast system that delivers the same message
            to many subscribers at the same time.

    --------------------------------------------------
    WHAT IS AN SNS TOPIC?
    --------------------------------------------------

        A Topic is a channel where messages are published.

        Example:
            Topic Name → "HighCPUAlerts"

        You publish one message → all subscribers receive it.

        A topic is like a WhatsApp group:
            You send one message,
            everyone in the group gets it.

    --------------------------------------------------
    WHAT IS A SUBSCRIPTION?
    --------------------------------------------------

        A subscription is where the topic sends messages.

        You can subscribe:
            • Email
            • SMS
            • Lambda
            • SQS
            • HTTP endpoint
            • Mobile push

        Example:
            Topic: "Server-Alerts"
            Subscriptions:
                - devops-team@gmail.com
                - +91-9000000000 (SMS)
                - A Lambda function

        When the topic receives a message,
        all subscribers get the notification.


----------------------------------------

        SNS = Messaging or notification system  
        Topic = Message channel  
        Subscription = Delivery target (email/SMS/Lambda/etc.)  

        Publish once → Delivered to many.


========================================

    WHAT IS AN AUTO SCALING GROUP (ASG)?

    --------------------------------------------------
    SIMPLE DEFINITION
    --------------------------------------------------

        An Auto Scaling Group (ASG) is something  which  automatically adds or removes EC2 instances
        based on load, traffic, or health.

        Meaning:
            - When load increases → ASG adds servers --- Scale out 
            - When load decreases → ASG removes servers  --- Scale In 
            - If a server fails → ASG replaces it automatically


    --------------------------------------------------
    WHY ASG IS USED?
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Handles traffic spikes automatically  
        • Maintains high availability  
        • Keeps a minimum number of servers running  
        • Saves cost by scaling down during low traffic  
        • Replaces unhealthy instances automatically  


    --------------------------------------------------
    HOW ASG WORKS (SIMPLE FLOW)
    --------------------------------------------------

        1. You create a Launch Template (EC2 blueprint)
        2. Create an Auto Scaling Group using that template
        3. Set:
               - Minimum capacity
               - Desired capacity
               - Maximum capacity
        4. ASG launches EC2 instances
        5. ASG performs health checks
        6. ASG scales out or scales in based on traffic


    --------------------------------------------------
    IMPORTANT TERMS
    --------------------------------------------------

        Min capacity:
            Lowest number of EC2s the ASG will maintain.

        Desired capacity:
            The number of EC2s ASG tries to keep running normally.

        Max capacity:
            The highest number of EC2s ASG is allowed to launch.

        Scaling out:
            Adding more EC2s when load increases.

        Scaling in:
            Removing EC2s when load decreases.


    --------------------------------------------------
    WHAT YOU NEED TO CREATE AN ASG
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Launch Template  
        • VPC + Subnets  
        • Target Group (optional but recommended)  
        • Load Balancer (optional, usually ALB)  
        • Scaling Policies (optional)  


    --------------------------------------------------
    ASG CONFIGURATION OPTIONS (EXPLAINED SIMPLY)
    --------------------------------------------------

        1. Launch Template
            Includes AMI, instance type, key pair, user data, security groups.

        2. Network (VPC + Subnets)
            Select 2 or more AZs for high availability.

        3. Load Balancer Attachment (optional)
            Connect your ASG to:
                - Application Load Balancer (ALB)
                - Network Load Balancer (NLB)

        4. Health Check Types
            • EC2 status checks  
            • ELB health checks (recommended for ALB/NLB)  

        5. Scaling Policies
            a) Target Tracking:
                   Example: keep CPU at 50%  
            b) Step Scaling:
                   Add/remove EC2s as thresholds are crossed  
            c) Scheduled Scaling:
                   Scale based on time (office hours, weekends)

        6. Instance Protection
            Blocks ASG from terminating selected EC2 instances.

        7. Notifications (optional)
            Sends SNS alerts when scaling events happen.


    --------------------------------------------------
    EXAMPLE SCENARIO
    --------------------------------------------------

        Min capacity      = 2  
        Desired capacity  = 4  
        Max capacity      = 10  

        Traffic increases → ASG scales to 7  
        Traffic drops     → ASG scales back to 4  
        An instance fails → ASG launches a new one automatically  


    --------------------------------------------------
    HEALTH CHECK BEHAVIOR
    --------------------------------------------------

        Instance is considered unhealthy if:
            • Fails EC2 status checks  
            • Fails ALB/NLB health checks  
            • Stops, crashes, or becomes unreachable  

        ASG will terminate the failed instance
        and create a new one automatically.


    --------------------------------------------------
    SUMMARY


        Auto Scaling Group:
            - Launches EC2 instances automatically
            - Replaces unhealthy instances
            - Scales up during high traffic
            - Scales down to save cost
            - Ensures high availability



