DATE: 12 FEB 2026

AWS MINI PROJECT 


https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/vpc-example-private-subnets-nat.html




    AWS NETWORKING CONCEPTS     (Inside Amazon Web Services (AWS))


    --------------------------------------------------
    1) VPC (Virtual Private Cloud)
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Your private network inside AWS.
        • You control:
              - IP address range (CIDR)
              - Subnets
              - Route tables
              - Security
        • Like your own data center in the cloud.


    --------------------------------------------------
    2) SUBNET
    --------------------------------------------------

        • A smaller network inside a VPC.
        • Created from the VPC IP range.
        • Lives inside one Availability Zone.


    --------------------------------------------------
    3) PUBLIC SUBNET
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Subnet that has a route to Internet Gateway.
        • Instances here can access the internet directly.
        • Usually used for:
              - Load Balancer
              - Bastion Host
              - Web servers


    --------------------------------------------------
    4) PRIVATE SUBNET
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Subnet that does NOT have direct internet access.
        • No route to Internet Gateway.
        • Used for:
              - Application servers
              - Databases
              - Internal services


    --------------------------------------------------
    5) INTERNET GATEWAY (IGW)
    --------------------------------------------------

        • A gateway that allows communication
          between VPC and the internet.
        • Attached to the VPC.
        • Required for public internet access.


    --------------------------------------------------
    6) NAT GATEWAY
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Allows private subnet instances
          to access the internet (OUTBOUND only).
        • Prevents internet from initiating
          connections to private instances.
        • Used for:
              - OS updates
              - Downloading packages


    --------------------------------------------------
    7) ROUTE TABLE
    --------------------------------------------------

        • A set of rules that decides
          where network traffic should go.
        • Each subnet must be associated
          with a route table.

        Example:
            10.0.0.0/16 → local
            0.0.0.0/0   → igw-id


    --------------------------------------------------
    8) PUBLIC ROUTE TABLE
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Has route:
              0.0.0.0/0 → Internet Gateway
        • Used by public subnets.


    --------------------------------------------------
    9) PRIVATE ROUTE TABLE
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Does NOT have direct IGW route.
        • May have:
              0.0.0.0/0 → NAT Gateway
        • Used by private subnets.


    --------------------------------------------------
    10) JUMP SERVER / BASTION HOST
    --------------------------------------------------

        • An EC2 instance placed in public subnet.
        • Used to SSH into private servers.
        • Acts as a secure entry point.

        Flow:
            Your Laptop → Bastion Host → Private EC2


    --------------------------------------------------
    COMPLETE FLOW SUMMARY
    --------------------------------------------------

        Internet
            ↓
        Internet Gateway
            ↓
        Public Subnet (ALB / Bastion)
            ↓
        Private Subnet (App / DB)
            ↓
        NAT Gateway (for outbound internet)

        VPC contains everything.
